extracted_snippet:
{'original': 'Had a really lovely experience. We ordered the French toast, chocolate cake, croissant with butter, and cappuccinos — everything was delicious and beautifully presented.

The café was quite busy, but it never felt rushed or overwhelming, which made it easy to relax and enjoy the atmosphere. Service was excellent throughout — attentive, friendly, and efficient.

Definitely a spot worth visiting if you’re in Porto!'}

{'original': "It's old it's charming and it's friendly. Has a very nice menu and an extensive wine list. I had the ham and cheese croissant with a glass of white wine and to be fair is probably the one the nicest ham and cheese croissants I've ever had. I certainly had a few.

It's like a trip to another era, the staff addressed in wholesale uniforms. The maitre d, is very friendly and accommodating.

The decor is what you'd expect to be, old style and very ornate."}

{'original': 'Prices aee indeed pretty high here, but the food was great.

We ordered steak sandwich, 2 vegetable soups, toasts, sencha tea and a chocolate cake. Everything was tasty.

Service was also pretty goid despite it veing quite busy evening.'}

{'original': 'Visiting Café Majestic was a truly memorable experience. The atmosphere is absolutely enchanting — it feels like stepping back in time, with elegant decor and a unique historic charm that sets it apart from any other place in Porto. The service was excellent: attentive, professional, and very friendly, which made the visit even more enjoyable.

That said, I did find the prices to be quite high. While it might not be the most budget-friendly spot, I understand that part of what you’re paying for is the history and ambiance of this iconic café. For those who appreciate cultural heritage and a special setting, it may well be worth it.

All in all, it’s a beautiful place to visit at least once — for the experience, the history, and a taste of something truly classic.'}

{'original': 'The atmosphere makes this experience, other than that not much to it. Door Man was very polite however waiting staff were subpar, long waiting time from ordering to paying the bill.

Food was either under or over cooked. Lacking flavour and for the price you expect so much more. Consider the food edible and not much more. The Plating contrasts the beautiful decor unpleasantly.

Aside from its historical value and beautiful design, do not expect much more. Take a picture buy the cheapest thing and move on.'}

{'original': "I don't understand why anyone would pay 8€ for a subpar cappuccino when there are great affordable places nearby.
This place is a tourist trap if I've ever seen one. It's not so beautiful you can't skip it, it's packed with people, the staff clearly dislike being there and you pay the highest price I've ever seen for coffee and food that is worth a fraction of that.

It doesn't deserve the 4.1 at all."}

{'original': 'What a tourist trap!
The 9 euro double espresso and 6 euro americano are the worst coffee in my life ever. If you expect the historical and romantic vibe, you won’t find it either. I expected the New York Cafe in Budapest, but it’s way different.

완전 돗대기 시장이고 너무 맛이없으니 오지마시길'}

{'original': 'Piège à touristes.
Nous avons pris le menu et avons payé un total de 90€. Le jus d’orange n’est pas pressé, café avec beaucoup trop de bulles, les plats sont très normaux. Pour un café populaire，la qualité des produits par rapport au prix n’est pas bon du tout.', 'translated': "Tourist trap.

We ordered the set menu and paid a total of €90. The orange juice wasn't freshly squeezed, the coffee was far too fizzy, and the food was very ordinary. For a popular café, the quality of the food is very poor for the price."}

{'original': 'Tentei visitar e senti repulsa ao ver a postura dos garçons tratando os clientes como se fosse um favor nos atender!

O lugar é muito bonito, mas infelizmente sem vida!', 'translated': "I tried to visit and felt repulsed by the waiters' attitude, treating customers as if serving them was a favor!

The place is very beautiful, but unfortunately lifeless!"}

{'original': 'Tenia muy altas expectativas sobre este restaurant, fui a tomar un café con mi esposa y todo estuvo mal, el café muy malo, muy elegante el restaurant pero no saben servir un buen café ni hacer latte art, el pastel de nata se sentía viejo y el cheesecake dejaba mucho que desear.

Sus precios demasiados altos para el servicio que ofrecen. Nada recomendado', 'translated': "I had very high expectations for this restaurant. I went for coffee with my wife, and everything was bad. The coffee was terrible. The restaurant is very elegant, but they don't know how to serve good coffee or make latte art. The pastel de nata felt dated, and the cheesecake left a lot to be desired.

Their prices are too high for the service they offer. Not recommended at all."}

{'original': "The decor is the reason to come see this place. The food is definitely about double the normal price, which is what you'll be paying to sit in the decor.

Unfortunately, the food and drinks are not nearly up to par for the price. In fact, the nata was so below par that it was more than a waste of money.

There were no lines at about 20 minutes before opening, but lines are probably about 30 minutes even after about 20 minutes after opening. If you're going for the decor, be among the first to not waste the time."}

{'original': "Es una cafetería bonita, con buen personal, pero la comida deja mucho que desear. Pedí french toast majestic style y era muy difícil masticarlo. Muy duro y nada especial. Es trampa para turistas. Recomiendo comer en otro sitio.

It's a pretty cafetería with nice personal but the food is not worth It. I ordered french toast majestic style and It was dry and really hard to get through even with a knife.  It felt like a scam.", 'translated': "It's a pretty café with nice staff, but the food leaves much to be desired. I ordered the Majestic French toast, and it was very hard to chew. Very tough and nothing special. It's a tourist trap. I recommend eating somewhere else.

It's a pretty café with nice staff, but the food is not worth it. I ordered the Majestic French toast, and it was dry and really hard to chew, even with a knife. It felt like a rip-off."}

{'original': '맛이 특출 나지는 않지만 , 경험해볼만한 가치가 있는 공간
재방문 의사 있습니다 100년된 전통이 담긴 공간으로 저녁에는 피아노 연주도 합니다. 음료값이 전혀 아깝지 않습니다', 'translated': "The taste isn't exceptional, but it is a place worth the experience.

I would visit again. It is a space steeped in 100 years of tradition, and piano performances are held in the evenings. The price of the drinks is absolutely worth it."}
